{"change_summary":"No additional code edits were required in this apply-fixes round. The completion-round-15 review approved the milestone task-run lineage implementation without amendments, so I left the code unchanged and carried forward the validated state from the latest reviewed build.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Attempts that still omit `run_id` remain ambiguous for completion updates when multiple same-project runless attempts are open at once; this round preserves that audit history instead of collapsing it, but deterministic finalization still depends on richer caller metadata."],"steps":[{"description":"Reviewed the approved completion-round-15 validation output and confirmed there were no follow-up fixes or amendments to apply.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Left the existing milestone task-run lineage implementation unchanged because the approved review found no remaining defects requiring code changes.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Carried forward the approved validation evidence for formatting, milestone_record tests, clippy, and bead hygiene from the latest reviewed implementation.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Approved review evidence confirms `cargo fmt --all --check` passes with no formatting issues.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passes with 99 tests.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes cleanly.","Prior round validation evidence confirms `br lint` passed with no template warnings (`77 issues checked`)."]}